    \"sessionId\": \"1d30bc00-4063-4cb3-93bd-867f4e5be0cd\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 37954,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Administrator\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\main\\\\sessions\\\\1d30bc00-4063-4cb3-93bd-867f4e5be0cd.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The calendar and task APIs need user authorization. The user info came through fine though. I need to inform the user that they need to authorize the calendar and task permissions first. Let me check if there's a way to handle this - maybe I need to trigger the OAuth flow.\\n\\nActually, looking at the error \\\"need_user_authorization\\\", this means the user hasn't authorized the Feishu calendar/task permissions for this app. I should let them know about this and suggest they authorize the permissions.\\n\\nSince this is a cron job that's supposed to send a summary automatically, but the APIs require user auth, I should just report the issue in the response.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"今日行程概览（2026年3月20日，周五）\\n\\n⚠️ **权限不足，无法获取日程和任务**\\n飞书日历和任务功能需要您授权后才能访问。请回复\\\"授权\\\"或\\\"去授权\\\"，我将帮您完成飞书权限授权流程。\\n\\n授权完成后，我会自动为您发送今日行程概览 📋\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"minimax\",\n          \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 962,\n            \"output\": 204,\n            \"totalTokens\": 38158,\n            \"cacheRead\": 36992,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0.00217048\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1773961312389\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"count":3,"sessi